%20talking%20points.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cspan%3Ehis%20response%20to%20the%20US%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funvaccinated-child-dies-texas-measles-cases-surge-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emeasles%20outbreak%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20new%20secretary%20of%20health%2C%20Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20raised%20eyebrows%20by%20touting%20vitamin%20A%20as%20a%20possible%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20146%20people%20have%20been%20sickened%20and%20one%20child%20has%20died%20from%20the%20disease%2C%20which%20is%20spreading%20in%20West%20Texas%20and%20New%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%2C%20who%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-rfk-jr-plans-to-make-america-healthy-again-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopposed%20vaccine%20mandates%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20addressed%20the%20outbreak%20in%20an%20op-ed%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fopinion%2Frobert-f-kennedy-jr-measles-outbreak-call-action-all-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20he%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20MMR%20vaccine%20protects%20against%20the%20disease%2C%20he%20did%20not%20explicitly%20urge%20Americans%20to%20get%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funvaccinated-child-dies-texas-measles-cases-surge-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evaccinated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaying%20%26quot%3Bthe%20decision%20to%20vaccinate%20is%20a%20personal%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20also%20said%20the%20CDC%20released%20new%20guidance%20on%20using%20vitamin%20A%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eas%20a%20potential%20treatment%20for%20measles%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20well-balanced%20diet%20%26quot%3Bremains%20a%20best%20defense%20against%20most%20chronic%20and%20infectious%20illnesses.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20subsequent%20Fox%20News%20interview%2C%20he%20suggested%20treating%20measles%20with%20cod%20liver%20oil%2C%20a%20supplement%20high%20in%20vitamin%20A%20and%20vitamin%20D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20go%20down%20well%20with%20public%20health%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVitamin%20A%20is%20often%20touted%20by%20vaccine%20skeptics%2C%20including%20Children's%20Health%20Defense%2C%20the%20anti-vaccine%20organization%20Kennedy%20formerly%20chaired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20vitamin%20A%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20well-studied%20treatment%20for%20measles%2C%20doctors%20and%20researchers%20told%20Business%20Insider%20there's%20no%20evidence%20it%20can%20prevent%20the%20disease.%20They%20expressed%20concern%20that%20Kennedy's%20message%20may%20perpetuate%20a%20misconception%20that%20supplements%20could%20be%20an%20alternative%20to%20vaccinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20nearly%20a%20firm%20enough%20statement%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrea%20Love%2C%20an%20immunologist%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BGood%20nutrition%20and%20vitamin%20A%20are%20not%20going%20to%20stop%20a%20measles%20outbreak.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202d2030a-9717-4f6d-be2c-ce5c600bc174%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20does%20vitamin%20A%20protect%20against%20measles%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20vitamin%20A%20is%20used%20to%20treat%20patients%20with%20measles.%20Both%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20and%20the%20American%20Academy%20of%20Pediatrics%20recommend%20giving%20vitamin%20A%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nfid.org%2Fresource%2Fvitamin-a-for-the-management-of-measles-in-the-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeasles%20patients%20with%20vitamin%20deficiency%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20malnutrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeasles%20can%20deplete%20the%20body's%20supply%20of%20vitamin%20A%2C%20and%20kids%20deficient%20in%20vitamin%20A%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20more%20severe%20infections%20or%20complications%20like%20high%20fever%2C%20blindness%2C%20and%20even%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETherapeutic%20doses%20of%20vitamin%20A%20for%20measles%20range%20between%2015%2C000%20to%2060%2C000%20micrograms%20RAE%20per%20dose%20%E2%80%94%20much%20higher%20than%20the%20recommended%20daily%20amount%20for%20vitamin%20A%20in%20your%20diet%2C%20which%20is%20between%20700%20to%20900%20micrograms%20RAE.%20Cod%20liver%20oil%20is%20not%20a%20standard%20treatment%20for%20measles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVitamin%20A%20is%20less%20commonly%20administered%20for%20measles%20in%20the%20US%20where%20people%20tend%20to%20get%20too%20much%20vitamin%20A%20rather%20than%20too%20little.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrucially%2C%20dosing%20up%20on%20vitamin%20A%20supplements%20will%20not%20protect%20against%20a%20measles%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Sudfeld%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20nutrition%20at%20the%20Harvard%20T.H.%20Chan%20School%20of%20Public%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20author%20of%20a%20study%20that%20Kennedy%20cited%20in%20his%20Fox%20News%20op-ed%20%E2%80%94%20said%20research%20supports%20using%20vitamin%20A%20to%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20complications%20from%20measles%2C%20but%20he%20stressed%20that%20supplementing%20it%20won't%20protect%20against%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20best%20intervention%20we%20have%20to%20prevent%20measles%20is%20vaccination.%20The%20MMR%20vaccine%20is%20safe%20and%20effective%20for%20the%20prevention%20of%20measles%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f5d9df5-c453-45cb-a666-c6bd3ac73775%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EVitamin%20A%20can%20be%20toxic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20vitamin%20A%20is%20a%20major%20talking%20point%20for%20anti-vaccine%20advocates%2C%20who%20champion%20supplements%20as%20a%20protective%20measure%2C%20despite%20evidence%20to%20the%20contrary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Love%2C%20the%20immunologist%2C%20was%20frustrated%20with%20Kennedy's%20op-ed.%20She%20felt%20the%20resulting%20message%20could%20confuse%20readers%20who%20are%20already%20skeptical%20of%20vaccines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20who%20see%20this%20are%20going%20to%20pick%20up%20on%20the%20things%20that%20resonate%20with%20their%20beliefs%2C%26quot%3B%20Love%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20entire%20wellness%20industry%20and%20pseudoscience%20landscape%20plays%20into%20the%20idea%20of%20taking%20control%20of%20your%20health.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELove%20added%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fvitamin-a-toxicity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverdose%20on%20vitamin%20A%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20nutrient%20is%20fat-soluble%2C%20which%20means%20it%20can%20build%20up%20in%20the%20tissues%20over%20time.%20Too%20much%20can%20cause%20problems%20like%20headaches%2C%20fatigue%2C%20joint%20pain%2C%20liver%20damage%2C%20and%20reduced%20bone%20density.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20concern%20is%20people%20are%20going%20to%20start%20megadosing%20vitamin%20A%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20see%20an%20increase%20in%20toxicity%2C%26quot%3B%20Love%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gold%20standard%20of%20protection%20against%20measles%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-do-vaccines-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewidespread%20MMR%20vaccination%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20curtail%20the%20spread%20of%20the%20highly%20infectious%20virus.%20A%20vaccinated%20person%20can%20be%20infectious%20for%20days%20before%20they%20show%20symptoms%2C%20and%20their%20breath%20particles%20can%20linger%20in%20the%20air%20for%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20effective%20preventive%20measure%20is%20vaccination%2C%20that%20cannot%20be%20overemphasized%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Eduardo%20Villamor%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20epidemiology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20School%20of%20Public%20Health%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%